Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a splash of oil in a #saucepan{} over medium-high heat. Add half the baby plum tomatoes and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Add the garlic, cook for ~{1%minute}, then add the @puttanesca sauce{250}. Turn the heat to low and bubble gently until ready to use.

Pour the boiling water into a large pan and add a good pinch of @salt{}. Pop the pan onto high heat. Add the @spaghetti{200} to the boiling water and cook for ~{11%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @avocado{1}, remove the stone, remove the skin and cut the flesh into 2cm chunks and pop them in a #bowl{}. Add the remaining baby plum tomatoes and @wild rocket{40}. Mix the @balsamic vinegar{12} with the @honey{15} and @olive oil{2}(for the dressing).

When the spaghetti is cooked, drain into a #colander{}. Return to the pan and add the puttanesca sauce, basil and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40}. Mix well.

Pour the dressing over your salad just before serving. Toss to coat the leaves. Share the pasta between your bowls. Serve the dressed salad on the side and finish with leftover cheese.

> That looks amazing. We are sure you are eager to savour the results, but just pause for a moment to marvel at what you have achieved. Now eat!